---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/ui/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBlock from '../components/ui/CtaBlock.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Direct Connect Flight Academy"
  description="Direct Connect Flight Academy is an FAA Part 141 certificated flight school in Colorado Springs with Self-Examining Authority for Private and Instrument checkrides."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About DCFA"
    title="Built by airline pilots, for future airline pilots."
    subtitle="Direct Connect Flight Academy was founded with one goal: train pilots the way airlines actually fly, so the transition from student to professional is as short and smooth as possible."
    bgImage="/images/team/open-house.jpg"
  />

  <!-- Self-Examining Authority -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-950 py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-10 lg:gap-16">
        <div class="lg:col-span-1">
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase">Our advantage</div>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">FAA Self-Examining Authority</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            DCFA is one of only a small number of Part 141 schools in the United States to hold <strong>FAA Self-Examining Authority</strong> for Private Pilot and Instrument Rating checkrides.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            What that means in practice: when most students finish their training, they wait two to six weeks for a Designated Pilot Examiner (DPE) to be available for the checkride. During that wait, skills get rusty and timelines slip. At DCFA, we administer those checkrides ourselves, in-house, on our schedule. You finish when <em>you're</em> ready — not when an outside examiner has an opening.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            That single advantage compresses the timeline from Discovery Flight to Commercial Pilot by months. It's the most concrete differentiator between DCFA and almost any other flight school you'll consider.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Credentials -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Credentials and capabilities</h2>

      <div class="mt-10 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
        {[
          { title: 'FAA Part 141 Certificated', body: 'Structured curriculum approved by the FAA, with reduced minimum hours compared to Part 61 training.' },
          { title: 'Self-Examining Authority', body: 'In-house Private Pilot and Instrument checkrides. No DPE wait list.' },
          { title: 'Active Airline Pilot Mentors', body: 'Instructors are working Part 121 pilots, not time-builders. They know what comes next.' },
          { title: 'ATP-CTP with A320 Sim', body: 'Full-motion Airbus A320 simulator training in Dallas or Las Vegas as part of our $4,995 ATP-CTP program.' },
          { title: 'Rotor Transition Program', body: 'Customized fixed-wing pathways for military and civilian helicopter pilots.' },
          { title: 'VA Benefits Accepted', body: 'Chapters 30, 33, 1606, and 1607 for the Instrument and Commercial programs.' },
        ].map(c => (
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-950 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 p-5 sm:p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">{c.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">{c.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Partnerships in action -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-950 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase">Airline partnerships</div>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Partnerships in action.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
          Established pipelines to the flight deck — not just logos on a page, but real working relationships with carriers actively hiring our graduates.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 lg:gap-8">
        <article class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900">
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/images/team/frontier-team.jpg" alt="DCFA team with Frontier Airlines representatives" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 sm:p-7">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase">Announced 2023</div>
            <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Frontier Airlines</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">A direct pipeline to one of the country's largest ultra-low-cost carriers — built around airline-style training from day one.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900">
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/images/team/key-lime-partnership.jpg" alt="DCFA and Key Lime Air partnership announcement" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 sm:p-7">
            <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase">Announced 2019</div>
            <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Key Lime Air</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">A long-standing relationship with the regional carrier — a route to Part 121 hours and the right seat for graduates ready to fly the line.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-lg bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-900 p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Also partnered with GoJet Airlines.</strong> A regional carrier flying for United Express — another established pathway from DCFA training to a Part 121 cockpit.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Location advantage -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-950 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase">Location</div>
          <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Colorado Springs Airport</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Based at the Colorado Springs Airport (KCOS), where we benefit from over <strong>300 days of flying weather per year</strong> and immediate access to mountain, high-altitude, and Class C airspace operations — the kind of varied training environment that produces well-rounded pilots.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 p-5">
            <div class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1055 Aviation Way</div>
            <div class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Colorado Springs, CO 80916</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="aspect-[4/3] rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800">
            <img src="/images/aircraft/da42-ground.png" alt="DA42 twin-engine aircraft at Colorado Springs Airport" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBlock />
</BaseLayout>
